                        <summary>
                            
                            <p>On the south base of the central shrine in the Madhyasthanāthēśvara temple.</p>						
                            
                            <p>Kulō[ttuṅga] [III ?]. Year lost.</p>						
                            
                            <p>The details of date available in the inscription are ba. 13, Thursday, Aviṭṭam which are insufficient to calculate the equivalent.</p>						
                            
                            <p>It mentions a gift of land to god Tirunāgīśvaramuḍai[ya Nāyaṉār] of Tiruppālaipandal on the southern bank of the river Peṇṇai by Kiḷiyūr Malaiyamāṉ Sūriyadēvaṉ Ni[la]ē[ṟṟa] Perumāḷ Edirigaṇāyaṉ <hi rend="italic">alias</hi> Śōḻaṅ[ga]adēvan.</p>						
                            
                        </summary>
